description: Elon Musk’s Grok chatbot has limited some of its Imagine image generation features to paid X subscribers, days after international uproar over the AI tool responded to user requests by “digitally undressing” people, including children.

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump continued his escalating threats towards Greenland, telling reporters that if he is not able to make a deal to acquire the Arctic territory “the easy way” then he will have to “do it the hard way.”
title: Trump wants deal with Greenland ‘whether they like it or no’

description: Four astronauts will come home from the International Space Station more than a month ahead of schedule. CNN's Jackie Wattles explains what we know about this rare early return. #nasa #astronauts #cnn

author: CNN
description: CNN's Randi Kaye reports new details about the ICE officer who shot and killed Renee Nicole Good in Minneapolis on Wednesday. The officer, identified in court documents as Jonathan Ross, was previously involved in another incident, where he was dragged after getting his arm trapped in a vehicle while trying to make an arrest.
title: ICE officer who shot Minneapolis woman previously injured in traffic stop

description: Tom Rehkopf, also known as “Typewriter Tom,” is a collector and repairman on a mission: to bring manual typewriters back. He visits schools and even started a local club to educate younger generations and bring typewriters back to homes everywhere. #CNN #style #typewriter
title: How typewriters are making a comeback

author: CNN
description: In a presentation to an oversight commission, an architect revealed new details about President Trump’s proposed East Wing expansion, including plans for a “grand stair,” additional space for utilities and food service, and a proposed second-story addition to the West Wing Colonnade. Trump has said the entire cost for the project will be covered by private donors. CNN’s Betsy Klein reports.
title: Architect reveals plans for new White House East Wing

author: CNN
description:
Video captured by ICE agent Jonathan Ross gives a raw, up-close perspective of the pivotal moments surrounding his fatal shooting Wednesday of Renee Good in Minneapolis. Warning: The video is disturbing.

Protests and vigils have occurred nationwide after the agent fatally shot the Minneapolis mother, deepening tensions over the Trump administration’s immigration crackdown.

CNN senior correspondent Josh Campbell analyzes the video, and CNN law enforcement correspondent Whitney Wild reports on protests in Hennepin County, Minnesota, just outside Minneapolis.

author: CNN
description: Almost a week after the US captured Nicolás Maduro, the response from citizens in Venezuelans has remained largely quiet. Journalist Mary Triny Mena went out in the country’s capital, Caracas, to try to get a better sense of how Venezuelans are feeling right now. #cnn #cnnnews
title: Hear from Venezuelans after Maduro's capture

author: CNN
description:
The US economy added just 50,000 jobs in December, according to the latest monthly report from the Bureau of Labor Statistics. The unemployment rate ticked down to 4.4% from a revised 4.5%. The latest data means 2025 saw the weakest annual job growth since 2003, with just 584,000 jobs added last year. Stocks opened higher Friday as investors digested the latest data on the US labor market. 

CNN's Matt Egan reports, and John Berman speaks with Rep. Mike Lawler (R-NY), who sits on the House Financial Services Committee.

0:00 New jobs numbers
0:37 CNN correspondent reports
4:52 GOP congressman on jobs report

#JobsReport #Economy #News
title: Jobs report: Just 50K jobs added last month, unemployment rate falls

author: CNN
description: Chinese state and social media have been abuzz with talk about the US operation against Venezuela. Some have speculated that it could inform China's calculation regarding Taiwan. CNN's senior international correspondent Will Ripley explains why.
title: Is China looking at Venezuela as a blueprint for action on Taiwan?

author: CNN
description: A new press-on nail system can switch between more than 400 colors using a smartphone app. The technology was unveiled by digital beauty startup iPolish, which has opened preorders for a $95 starter kit set to ship in summer 2026. #cnn #news
title: These app-controlled nails change color in seconds

author: CNN
description: In a mob attack on Thursday afternoon, a group of Israeli settlers beat an elderly deaf man and torched cars during a mob attack in a Palestinian village in the occupied West Bank. Surveillance footage shows several settlers attacking the man with clubs while others run up and kick him while he’s on his knees. CNN’s Jeremy Diamond reports. #cnn #news
title: Deaf Palestinian man beaten by Israeli settlers

description: An avalanche of garbage buried workers at a waste segregation facility in the central Philippines, killing one person and leaving 38 others missing, according to officials.

author: CNN
description:
Chronic disease, anxiety, ADHD, and even the shape of a person's face could be consequences of dysfunctional breathing. And most of us, it turns out, are doing it wrong – but it’s never too late to fix it. Sanjay sits down with journalist James Nestor to discuss the fifth anniversary edition of Breath: The New Science of a Lost Art, and how simple changes to the way we breathe can start improving our health right away.

Listen to the full episode on CNN's Chasing Life podcast: https://swap.fm/clsgyt010926

#news #cnn #health #breathing #breath #lungs
title: Why you’re breathing wrong and how to fix it | Chasing Life

title: Chloe Kim injured ahead of Olympics

title: Is your dog secretly eavesdropping?

author: CNN
description: BTS is poised for a huge 2026, reuniting after an almost four-year hiatus. And the band has signaled its long-awaited comeback with three mysterious red circles. The symbols first appeared on a postcard sent by the K-pop stars to their “Gold” fans – some of the most dedicated among their fanbase, which is known as ARMY. Since then, BTS has announced a new album, and next week will release world tour dates. In the meantime, ARMY has tried to decode the symbols’ hidden meaning. #CNN #News #BTS #ARMY
title: The three dots sending BTS fans wild

description:
Singer, poet, author Patti Smith has experienced the deaths of her husband, guitarist Fred “Sonic” Smith, her brother Todd, and her lifelong friend and artistic soulmate, photographer Robert Mapplethorpe. Time doesn’t heal those "sacred wounds," she tells Anderson, but in time, you can learn to navigate it more.

Join the community to share your story and watch Anderson's weekly streaming show All There Is Live at https://cnn.com/allthereis
title: Patti Smith on the ‘sacred wounds’ of grief
